T~L~115~85~0~#0000FF~~9pt~~~~comment~GPSDO
- GPSDO Rx and Tx reverse at RPi side
- 3v3 to voltage on signal level converter from GPSDO and for ublox should be taken from RPi not Pico
 
- PDIV Rx and Tx pins reverse at PicoController side
- Add jumper header in front of any 3v3 or 5v pins of RPi of the Pico
- connect CLKIND to GPIO22 of the control module
- reverse MISO and MOSI pin from BMP280 at the RPi site.
- REFCLK is from CM1 Divider or CM2 trig divider
- R_RI connector has to be vertically flipped. All pins are wrong, as the RPi is bottom-up.
- check UART pinout https://pinout.xyz/pinout/uart (PicoTX GPIO0 should be GPIO1 pin 28 (RxT) at RPi)
- create connection from RPi to RPi Pico for HW reset
- add antenna voltage jumper, you it can be turned off
- 4k7 odpory na SCL a SDA linky, s jumperom pre ich vyradenie (na pullup 3v3 rail)
- wire the Controller Pico module serial port to RPI4 GPIO4/5 (most basic serial port with UART support, not software)
 
- mainboard have to have male connectors pin, and the devices female (holes)
- konektory TP1/TP2 na opacnu stranu Citaca, vedla ublox
- accelerometer port
- status neopixel to RPi4~1~start~gge8377~0~pinpart
